{"id":236453,"date":"2024-02-02T08:51:01","date_gmt":"2024-02-02T03:21:01","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/?p=236453"},"modified":"2024-02-02T09:00:21","modified_gmt":"2024-02-02T03:30:21","slug":"subodh-kant-sahay","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/subodh-kant-sahay\/","title":{"rendered":"Subodh Kant Sahay Wiki, Age, Caste, Wife, Family, Biography &amp; More"},"content":{"rendered":"<p><a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/02\/Subodh-Kant-Sahay-.jpg\"><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-236494\" src=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/02\/Subodh-Kant-Sahay-.jpg\" alt=\"Subodh Kant Sahay\" width=\"516\" height=\"473\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/02\/Subodh-Kant-Sahay-.jpg 516w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/02\/Subodh-Kant-Sahay--300x275.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 516px) 100vw, 516px\" \/><\/a><\/p>\n<p>Subodh Kant Sahay is an Indian politician who represented the Ranchi constituency in Jharkhand and served as a Member of Parliament for three terms. As a member of the Indian National Congress, he has held significant positions, including that of Cabinet Minister for Tourism until 28 October 2012.<\/p>\n<div id=\"ez-toc-container\" class=\"ez-toc-v2_0_62 counter-hierarchy ez-toc-counter ez-toc-custom ez-toc-container-direction\">\n<p class=\"ez-toc-title\">Contents<\/p>\n<label for=\"ez-toc-cssicon-toggle-item-65bce132960d4\" class=\"ez-toc-cssicon-toggle-label\"><span class=\"\"><span class=\"eztoc-hide\" style=\"display:none;\">Toggle<\/span><span class=\"ez-toc-icon-toggle-span\"><svg style=\"fill: #000000;color:#000000\" xmlns=\"http:\/\/www.w3.org\/2000\/svg\" class=\"list-377408\" width=\"20px\" height=\"20px\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\"><path d=\"M6 6H4v2h2V6zm14 0H8v2h12V6zM4 11h2v2H4v-2zm16 0H8v2h12v-2zM4 16h2v2H4v-2zm16 0H8v2h12v-2z\" fill=\"currentColor\"><\/path><\/svg><svg style=\"fill: #0000